                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.513/52: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative on Special Mission in Cuba</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crowder</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-05-19T13:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 19, 1922—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:11 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>28. Please communicate to Captain Demetrio Castillo<note n="34" xml:id="d844fn34"
                        >Liaison officer between President Zayas and General Crowder’s
                        mission.</note> at the Army and Navy Club and prior to his interview with
                    the Secretary on Monday the following: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Please stress to Secretary Hughes difficulties here in the way of
                            securing compliance with memorandum number 8, memorandum number 10,
                            reform of the national lottery with the contents of which you are
                            familiar and which was submitted to President Zayas May 15th; also the
                            amount of contractual indebtedness Department of Public Works and
                            difficulty in readjusting these contracts. Particularly do I desire you
                            to stress to the Secretary the two unsuccessful efforts to get from the
                            Government here a dependable national audit and that we are still
                            without an itemization of either the outstanding floating debt or the
                            annual deficit for the current fiscal year. Explain to the Secretary the
                            general character of the reform in the army budget and the little we may
                            expect in the reform of the fixed budget.”<note n="35" xml:id="d844fn35"
                                >Notation on the telegram states that this message was communicated
                                to Captain Castillo by telephone.</note>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crowder</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
